2_6	0.0	Studying endocrine disruption of animals dating back over a century is novel.
2_7	0.05	Cricket frogs, once abundant, declined dramatically around Chicago and other regions in the 1960s, and the scientists found that the times and places with high rates of hermaphrodites, also called intersexes, overlapped with when and where the frogs disappeared in Illinois.
